Christmas Eve 2023 will forever go down as one of the hardest days I’ve ever experienced in my life. After a painful battle with cancer my beloved Gramps passed on to the next chapter. He was a father, husband, brother, grandfather, great grandfather, and the best you could ask for in all departments. He was an avid Michigan Wolverines fanatic, animal lover and nature buff. He sparked my interest in reptiles and exotic creatures very early on in life. He financially supported my skateboarding career since the early beginnings at the tender age of 9. He was extremely opinionated, hard headed and stubborn in his ways. I got my roughness from him, we make the same facial expressions. He treated my skateboarding career as if it was the Super Bowl, always my biggest supporter and biggest fan. He believed in me whenever I didn’t even believe in myself and always told me to snap out of it and reach for the stars. I’ll miss you ordering Grammy around in the kitchen, all your amazing food, telling you about my travel experiences, and just being in your presence in the physical form. You made my sisters and I’s lives so happy and fulfilling since we were children and into our adulthood. Every single accomplishment, milestone, experience I have from this day forward will be in your honor. I can only hope to be half the man you ever were, and if I’m able to do that I’ll consider myself a success. The last words he ever said to me were “Love you Code”. I’ll cherish those words and hold them close to my heart until my dying day. Thank you so much for being the best Grandpa I could ever dream of having. I know your spirit is with me everywhere I go and you’re going to make sure I’m always OK, as you have since I was born. I love you so much Grampy and knowing you’re not in anymore pain puts a smile on my face. It’s not goodbye but it’s see you later. Debba Debba Debba forever ❤️
